	<issue id="DE-60" type="general" linkend="" status="closed" category="major_technical" by="DE-60" date="2004-09-21" seds="no" ballot="PLCS DIS ballot" ballot_comment="yes" ballot_comment_id="DE-60" member_body="GE" resolution="accept">
		<issue_management owner="Nigel Shaw" priority="low" category="Task"/>
		<description>
			<p>
				<b>SC4 part number:</b>
			</p>
			<p>
				<b>(2) Clause:</b> 10303-1262
 </p>
			<p>
				<b>(3) Paragraph:</b> 4.3.13, 4.3.14
 </p>
			<p>
				<b>(5) Comment:</b>
			</p>
			<p>
Entity task must be a subtype of activity instead of activity_method. Also task_assignment must be subtype of applied_activity_assignment Otherwise we would have a major conflict with AP214.
</p>
			<p>
				<b>(6) Proposal:</b>
			</p>
			<p>
Do as proposed and map ARM action to executed_action and ARM task_assignment to applied_action_assignment.
Consequently further changes on task_state_relationship and others are needed to complete this.</p>
		</description>
		<comment by="Nigel Shaw" date="04-09-22">
			<description>
Task_specification in PLCS is satisfying the business requirement to
represent a set of instruction that may be carried out many times in the future. An
activity is used to represent each time that it is performed. This
distinction is in line with the STEP integrated resources.
</description>
		</comment>
		<comment by="Nigel Shaw" date="04-10-06">
			<description>
	   After long discussion, a major concern arises that the module should be harmonised with the AP214 representation of process plans. 
	   It was suggested that this be raised to WG12.
</description>
		</comment>
		<comment by="Nigel Shaw" date="04-10-18">
			<description>
				<p>Proposed solution is rejected.</p>
				<p>After further discussion with repesentatives of AP224 and AP214 it was agreed that the names used for some entities in this module's ARM cause confusion and should be renamed. As a consequence, Task will become Task_method, task_method will become Task_method_element and Task_result will become Task_objective. The Task_method.methods will become Task_method.elements. Other changes as need for consistency. Changes to entity definitions and mappings to correspond.
   </p>
			</description>
		</comment>
		<comment by="Sean Barker" date="04-11-1">
			<description>
			Implemented as Shaw 04-10-18 above, with consistent application throughout module, at ARM and MIM levels. Following discussions at Seattle, additional subtypes were added in the MIM for relationships, and the mappings had some additional 'magic strings' to facilitiate analysis of a MIM based exchange.
			</description>
		</comment>
